Step 4: Dockerizing Your Flask app

We'll create a Dockerfile so jenkins  can build a container image successfully 


Create a Dockerfile in your project folder devops-todo-app and push it to the git

name it Dockerfile

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Test the Docker build locally 

docker build -t devops-todo-app:latest .  #tells Docker build a new image from the instruction in your dockerfile
                                           -t [tag] it gives your image a name and a tag latest
 (if you donot give the name docker will give a random name which is hard to read name)

docker run -p 5000:5000 devops-todo-app    #This runs a containers
                                           #This maps the hostport:containersport  next the image name
then open :
http://localhost:5000

YOu should see :
welcome to Devops ToDo App!

if its work its perfect
_________________________________
To see the image you have built use the command:
 
==>docker images
------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Rebuild in jenkins

Now go back to your jenkins dashboard  -> open your devops-todo-app  job(pipeline)-> click build again 

This time ,jenkins will:
1.checkout your code 
2.install dependencies
3.build Docker image successsfully 
4.Push it to Docker HUb 


